  "text": "Samsung 990 EVO Plus $130 $140 Save $10 Storage capacity 1TB, 2TB, 4TB Hardware Interface PCIe Gen 4 x4 / Gen 5 x2 TBW 600TB per TB DRAM N/A Warranty 5 year An affordable, high-quality M.2 SSD from Samsung that's perfect for your next desktop PC or laptop upgrade. Get this 2TB model right now as it drops to its best price at just $130. Samsung makes some of the best SSD storage that you can buy right now. Of course, that means paying top dollar for the best performance you'll find, but sometimes, you just don't need that when you're looking to upgrade for cheap. That's where Samsung's 990 Evo Plus series comes in, providing a more affordable line of M.2 SSDs that still deliver great performance. Related Samsung 990 Evo Plus review: Somewhat speedier Samsung storage Samsung's latest mainstream M.2 NVMe SSD is good enough, but the competition is strong at this price point. With that said, you can now grab the 2TB model from Amazon as it drops to its best price at just $130. While the discount isn't all that steep from its current retail price, this is the lowest price we've seen for this model to date, making it a fantastic time to pick one up if you've been thinking about upgrading the storage on your laptop, desktop, or supported game console. What's great about the Samsung 990 Evo Plus SSD? So what do you get with Samsung's 990 Evo Plus SSD? Well, let's talk about the performance first, because that's most likely going to be an important point if you're thinking about picking this up. The 990 Evo Plus manages to deliver reasonable performance, with sequential read speeds of up to 7,250 and sequential write speeds that max out at 6,300MB/s. Not bad at all for the price that you're paying, and what's even better is that this drive is compatible with Gen5 M.2 slots, with the only caveat being that it only works on two channels. Of course, it does work on Gen4 hardware as well, making it ideal for a variety of different hardware like desktops and laptops. In addition, you can also use it in some game consoles as well, like popular PC gaming handhelds, along with the PlayStation 5. Another things to note about this SSD is that it does not have DRAM, which could be a dealbreaker for some. As far as reliability, Samsung provides a long five-year warranty on this drive, which should provide some peace of mind. Just be sure to grab it at this price while you can, or check out some other popular M.2 SSDs that we love. Although the pricing might be more expensive than the Samsung 990 Evo Plus, you might find something that's worth the extra money.",
