e\n\t\u003c/h5\u003e\n\n                                                    \n                \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eSamsung\u0026#39;s latest mainstream M.2 NVMe SSD is good enough, but the competition is strong at this price point.\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\n\n                    \n\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n                \t\n\n\n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWith that said, you can now grab the 2TB model from Amazon as it drops to its best price at just $130. While the discount isn\u0026#39;t all that steep from its current retail price, this is the lowest price we\u0026#39;ve seen for this model to date, making it a fantastic time to pick one up if you\u0026#39;ve been thinking about upgrading the storage on your laptop, desktop, or supported game console.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"what-39-s-great-about-the-samsung-990-evo-plus-ssd\"\u003e\n                        What\u0026#39;s great about the Samsung 990 Evo Plus SSD?\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \n    \n\u003cp\u003eSo what do you get with Samsung\u0026#39;s 990 Evo Plus SSD? Well, let\u0026#39;s talk about the performance first, because that\u0026#39;s most likely going to be an important point if you\u0026#39;re thinking about picking this up. The 990 Evo Plus manages to deliver reasonable performance, with sequential read speeds of up to 7,250 and sequential write speeds that max out at 6,300MB/s. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eNot bad at all for the price that you\u0026#39;re paying, and what\u0026#39;s even better is that this drive is compatible with Gen5 M.2 slots, with the only caveat being that it only works on two channels. Of course, it does work on Gen4 hardware as well, making it ideal for a variety of different hardware like desktops and laptops. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eIn addition, you can also use it in some game consoles as well, like \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/best-pc-gaming-handhelds/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003epopular PC gaming handhelds\u003c/a\u003e, along with the PlayStation 5. Another things to note about this SSD is that \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/how-important-dram-ssd/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eit does not have DRAM\u003c/a\u003e, which could be a dealbreaker for some. As far as reliability, Samsung provides a long five-year warranty on this drive, which should provide some peace of mind. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eJust be sure to grab it at this price while you can, or check out some other \u003ca href=\"http://www.xda-developers.com/best-m-2-ssd/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003epopular M.2 SSDs that we love\u003c/a\u003e. Although the pricing might be more expensive than the Samsung 990 Evo Plus, you might find something that\u0026#39;s worth the extra money. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                                            \n\n\n\n\n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
